Former presidential aide Reno Omokri has condemned the popular assertion that “behind every successful man is a woman. He argued the assertion, which explains that a ‘man’s achievements are made possible by the support and work of their wife or a female partner’ is absolutely false. Reno however, argued that behind every successful man are many unsuccessful years but definitely not a woman.   Fave takes over from Asa as Spotify Equal Music ambassador     Oshara releases new single     Lady Donli: Sacrifice I made for my music   “Dear men, Behind every successful man, there is not a woman. That proverb is a gigantic lie!” he tweeted. “Rather, behind almost every successful man, are very many unsuccessful years. He added: “And if he had focused on women in those years, his present success would not have manifested.”